naturalnumber.def:
The set of Natural numbers.
These are all positive whole numbers: 1, 2, 3, 4...

realnumber.def:
The set of Real numbers.
These are all positive and negative numbers; including fractions, decimals and even numbers which cannot be expressed in these forms, such as Pi

integernumber.def: This denotes the set of Integer numbers. These are all whole positive and negative numbers: - 2, -1, 0, 1, 2

rationalnumber.def: This denotes the set of Rational numbers. These are all positive and negative numbers which can be expressed as a fraction: -1/2, 0, 1, 5/7

coefficient.def: The number which an unknown term is being mulipled by. With 5x^2, 5 is the co-efficient of x^2
